# Repo conventions

```
services/patients/   Java clinical core
services/go/         intake | scheduling | notification (one Go module)
infra/               CDK (BackendStack + FrontendStack)
web/                 Next.js static export, PT-BR/EN
docs/                productization, architecture, deployment
scripts/build-go.sh  Go → dist/<svc>/bootstrap (linux/arm64)
```

## Build locally
- Go: `./scripts/build-go.sh` and `go test ./...` in `services/go`
- Java: `mvn -q package` in `services/patients` → `target/patients-service.jar`
- Web: `npm ci && npm run build` in `web` → `web/out`
- Infra: `npm ci && npx cdk synth` in `infra` (needs built Go/Java artifacts for full deploy)

## Patterns
- Domain events: `levecare.*` source, detail types like `intake.completed`, `booking.confirmed`, `prescription.issued`.
- Java: shaded jar for Lambda (not Boot repackage); SnapStart via published version + alias.
- Go: structured `slog` JSON; SES sandbox sends to verified `NOTIFY_EMAIL`.
- DynamoDB keys: `pk` / `sk` single-table per service.
- API: public `POST/GET /intake`, `GET /slots`; JWT for `/patients*`, `/bookings*`.

